 \"score\": 0.631133645775807, \"rank\": 0.584437305476831, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Rumours\", \"from\": 3604, \"to\": 3611}, {\"ngram\": \"that cardboard beds\", \"from\": 3643, \"to\": 3662}, {\"ngram\": \"any sudden movements\", \"from\": 3704, \"to\": 3724}, {\"ngram\": \"an attempt\", \"from\": 3726, \"to\": 3736}, {\"ngram\": \"romantic endeavours\", \"from\": 3751, \"to\": 3770}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They were dismissed, at both Games, as \\\"fake news\\\" andi's platonic testing backed up suggestions that the beds (built to support 240kg) will withstand even the most vigorous activities - and frankly the suggestion that the planet's fastest, strongest and most flexible people are not capable of having sex somewhere other than a bed is more than a little absurd.\", \"from\": 3773, \"to\": 4135, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"both Games\", \"from\": 3797, \"to\": 3807}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"fake news\\\" andi's platonic testing\", \"from\": 3812, \"to\": 3847}, {\"ngram\": \"suggestions\", \"from\": 3858, \"to\": 3869}, {\"ngram\": \"the beds\", \"from\": 3875, \"to\": 3883}, {\"ngram\": \"240kg\", \"from\": 3902, \"to\": 3907}, {\"ngram\": \"even the most vigorous activities\", \"from\": 3924, \"to\": 3957}, {\"ngram\": \"frankly the suggestion\", \"from\": 3964, \"to\": 3986}, {\"ngram\": \"the planet\", \"from\": 3992, \"to\": 4002}, {\"ngram\": \"sex\", \"from\": 4075, \"to\": 4078}, {\"ngram\": \"a bed\", \"from\": 4100, \"to\": 4105}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, the cardboard constructions, which when made up feel perfectly comfortable, are sustainable and recyclable solution to furnishing flats that will need to be emptied before new residents move in after the Games.\", \"from\": 4137, \"to\": 4356, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the cardboard constructions\", \"from\": 4146, \"to\": 4173}, {\"ngram\": \"sustainable and recyclable solution\", \"from\": 4226, \"to\": 4261}, {\"ngram\": \"flats\", \"from\": 4276, \"to\": 4281}, {\"ngram\": \"new residents\", \"from\": 4318, \"to\": 4331}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 4346, \"to\": 4355}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The phrase \\\"Olympic village\\\" is a misnomer of sorts, conjuring images of a sporting Glastonbury of tents, teepees and gazebos, whereas in reality, this is a brand new housing estate on the outskirts of central Paris.\", \"from\": 4358, \"to\": 4574, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4444, \"end\": 4455, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glastonbury\", \"score\": 0.9622397815119064, \"rank\": 0.0392420044102267, \"text\": \"Glastonbury\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glastonbury\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glastonbury\"}, {\"begin\": 4570, \"end\": 4575, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3686816891996459e-25, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The phrase\", \"from\": 4358, \"to\": 4368}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic village\", \"from\": 4370, \"to\": 4385}, {\"ngram\": \"a misnomer\", \"from\": 4390, \"to\": 4400}, {\"ngram\": \"sorts\", \"from\": 4404, \"to\": 4409}, {\"ngram\": \"images\", \"from\": 4421, \"to\": 4427}, {\"ngram\": \"tents\", \"from\": 4457, \"to\": 4462}, {\"ngram\": \"teepees\", \"from\": 4464, \"to\": 4471}, {\"ngram\": \"gazebos\", \"from\": 4476, \"to\": 4483}, {\"ngram\": \"reality\", \"from\": 4496, \"to\": 4503}, {\"ngram\": \"a brand new housing estate\", \"from\": 4513, \"to\": 4539}, {\"ngram\": \"the outskirts\", \"from\": 4543, \"to\": 4556}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The colour scheme is overwhelmingly beige, from the pavements made of seashells to the caramel apartment blocks that rise up to 10 storeys (but none above 20 metres) high over Saint-Ouen-sur-Seine, the post-industrial quarter a stone's throw from the Stade de France and just over four miles from the Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 4576, \"to\": 4890, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The colour scheme\", \"from\": 4576, \"to\": 4593}, {\"ngram\": \"the pavements\", \"from\": 4624, \"to\": 4637}, {\"ngram\": \"seashells\", \"from\": 4646, \"to\": 4655}, {\"ngram\": \"the caramel apartment blocks\", \"from\": 4659, \"to\": 4687}, {\"ngram\": \"up to 10 storeys\", \"from\": 4698, \"to\": 4714}, {\"ngram\": \"none\", \"from\": 4720, \"to\": 4724}, {\"ngram\": \"20 metres\", \"from\": 4731, \"to\": 4740}, {\"ngram\": \"Saint-Ouen-sur-Seine\", \"from\": 4752, \"to\": 4772}, {\"ngram\": \"the post-industrial quarter\", \"from\": 4774, \"to\": 4801}, {\"ngram\": \"a stone's throw\", \"from\": 4802, \"to\": 4817}, {\"ngram\": \"the Stade de France\", \"from\": 4823, \"to\": 4842}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 4873, \"to\": 4889}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the 1940s and 1950s, all the electricity for Paris's historic Metro system was generated in a plan which, now disused and repurposed, forms part of the village and will become an office block after the Games.\", \"from\": 4892, \"to\": 5103, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4942, \"end\": 4947, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3686816891996459e-25, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 1940s\", \"from\": 4895, \"to\": 4904}, {\"ngram\": \"1950s\", \"from\": 4909, \"to\": 4914}, {\"ngram\": \"all the electricity\", \"from\": 4916, \"to\": 4935}, {\"ngram\": \"a plan\", \"from\": 4987, \"to\": 4993}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 5035, \"to\": 5039}, {\"ngram\": \"the village\", \"from\": 5043, \"to\": 5054}, {\"ngram\": \"an office block\", \"from\": 5071, \"to\": 5086}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 5093, \"to\": 5102}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The village is bordered on one side by the Seine - in fact, part of the village has been built on an island in the river, complete with a new pedestrian bridge across from \\\"mainland Paris\\\".\", \"from\": 5105, \"to\": 5294, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5150, \"end\": 5155, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.026426891576244e-13, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 5289, \"end\": 5294, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3686816891996459e-25, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The village\", \"from\": 5105, \"to\": 5116}, {\"ngram\": \"one side\", \"from\": 5132, \"to\": 5140}, {\"ngram\": \"fact\", \"from\": 5159, \"to\": 5163}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 5165, \"to\": 5169}, {\"ngram\": \"the village\", \"from\": 5173, \"to\": 5184}, {\"ngram\": \"an island\", \"from\": 5203, \"to\": 5212}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 5216, \"to\": 5225}, {\"ngram\": \"a new pedestrian bridge\", \"from\": 5241, \"to\": 5264}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On another side, the eco-friendly neighbourhood is hemmed in by the busy A86, Paris's \\\"Super-peripherique\\\" secondary ring road, but organisers insist there is mitigation its potential impact.\", \"from\": 5296, \"to\": 5487, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5376, \"end\": 5381, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3686816891996459e-25, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"another side\", \"from\": 5299, \"to\": 5311}, {\"ngram\": \"the eco-friendly neighbourhood\", \"from\": 5313, \"to\": 5343}, {\"ngram\": \"the busy A86\", \"from\": 5360, \"to\": 5372}, {\"ngram\": \"organisers\", \"from\": 5428, \"to\": 5438}, {\"ngram\": \"mitigation\", \"from\": 5455, \"to\": 5465}, {\"ngram\": \"its potential impact\", \"from\": 5466, \"to\": 5486}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Large acoustic walls have been erected to protect residents from noise, and a huge machine, that looks like a space age mushroom, is being deployed to filter out the more dangerous and pollutive particles from the air.\", \"from\": 5488, \"to\": 5706, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Large acoustic walls\", \"from\": 5488, \"to\": 5508}, {\"ngram\": \"residents\", \"from\": 5538, \"to\": 5547}, {\"ngram\": \"noise\", \"from\": 5553, \"to\": 5558}, {\"ngram\": \"a huge machine\", \"from\": 5564, \"to\": 5578}, {\"ngram\": \"a space age mushroom\", \"from\": 5596, \"to\": 5616}, {\"ngram\": \"the more dangerous and pollutive particles\", \"from\": 5650, \"to\": 5692}, {\"ngram\": \"the air\", \"from\": 5698, \"to\": 5705}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That is an innovation though rather than a tried-and-tested piece of machinery, one of a number of experimental schemes that building company Solideo, the public sector organisation in charge of building the Olympic facilities, hopes will succeed and become a more widespread legacy of the Games.\", \"from\": 5708, \"to\": 6004, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an innovation\", \"from\": 5716, \"to\": 5729}, {\"ngram\": \"a tried-and-tested piece\", \"from\": 5749, \"to\": 5773}, {\"ngram\": \"machinery\", \"from\": 5777, \"to\": 5786}, {\"ngram\": \"a number\", \"from\": 5795, \"to\": 5803}, {\"ngram\": \"experimental schemes\", \"from\": 5807, \"to\": 5827}, {\"ngram\": \"building company Solideo\", \"from\": 5833, \"to\": 5857}, {\"ngram\": \"the public se